content:
In Flang, the sentence "The dog ate a cat" would be translated as "Fi flom fiko fa fol".

To break it down:
- "fi" is the definite article in Flang
- "flom" is the word for "dog" in Flang
- "fiko" is the past tense form of the verb "to eat" in Flang
- "fa" is the indefinite article in Flang
- "fol" is the word for "cat" in Flang

So, when we put it all together, we get "Fi flom fiko fa fol" which means "The dog ate a cat" in Flang. Let me know if you have any other questions or requests.
